# Running Rest-Adapter-Service-Extension in DevContainer

### Prerequisites
- Docker Deamon running

### In Visual Studio Code
- Run Command (`Ctrl + Shift + p`) DevContainers: Reopen in container 
- if required, select container .devcontainer from root directory

#### Build Project using gradle
Once container is opened, do
- open terminal (`Ctrl + j`)
- then run following commands to install java 8 and use it for current shell session
    - `sdk install java 8.0.442-tem` <br>
    - `sdk use java 8.0.442-tem`
- to build the project using gradle wrapper, run
    - `cd src`
    - `./gradlew build`
- view results (test and problems), run 
    - `cd build/reports/`
    - `python3 -m http.server 8090`
    - open `localhost:8090` in browser


See previous maven build, open `https://scans.gradle.com/s/znwgtirwnruxy/tests/overview`